@Vaer

I don't recall if we used QED with algebra only or also with geometry. My interest in math being what it was, I can't recall what problems we studied at what stage, exactly. We started with basic algebra and geometry, then came trigonometry, I think. Calculus may have been in the syllabus in the final year of high school, but I know nothing about it, so maybe not?

Btw. I have always thought freshman and junior was the same thing 🤣. Over here we just use numbers to describe years of study - pierwsza klasa, druga klasa, etc. (first class, second class, etc.) in primary and high school, and pierwszy rok, drugi rok, etc. (first year, second year, etc.) at university.

@Andrzej 
